&lt;NEW&gt;

RODIMUS smiled as he looked at TUSCON feeling so much like a knight
about to slide on his steed, a dragon rider. There was a certain look
of joy on his face, causing him to look more like HOR ROD of old for a
moment. &quot;Of course.&quot; he said.

Meanwhile LEO PRIME nodded to TUSCON, &quot;We will do what we can.
Airhammer gave me the cordinates where he saw the disturbance.&quot;

WING CALIBER handed LEO a PADD.

&quot;Hmmm.&quot; LEO said as he pursed his lips and read it. &quot;It was some
distance from here. I am sure you will reach it far faster than we
will.&quot;

There was a nod from RODIMUS, &quot;We&#39;ll be careful.&quot; He slid on the back
that TUSCON was offering.

&quot;You do that.&quot; LEO PRIME said. &quot;Have you thought about what we talked about?&quot;

A scowl flashed itself across RODIMUS&#39; face. &quot;Yes. We will discuss it
when I get back.&quot;

There was a grim look from LEO as WING CALIBER nodded as well,
evidently he knew the situation as well. &quot;Tuscon, we will talk as well
. . . when you return.&quot;

&quot;Very well then.&quot; LEO said. &quot;Tuscon keep us apprised of your
situation. Remember, you will be on your own for some time at the
distance you are going. The Fuzors are already out on patrol and I
will call them in as required, but if you run into more trouble than
you can handle it will take some time for them to reach your
position.&quot;

He paused thoughtfully, &quot;NIghtshift is still under repairs but should
be finished soon. Lord Elder should be ready as well as a few others.
We will all be ready and standing as a buffer.&quot;

As LEO talked WING CALIBER sent a communication link for NIGHTSHIFT to
report to their location once his repairs were complete, the same for
RAT TRAP and LORD ELDER. LEGACY was of course to remain where he was
as guardian of the Ark.

